$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Input Method

{ EnableHexNumpad #reg-EnableHexNumpad

  Setting this value to the (string) value of `1` allows to enter (hexadecimal) → development/Unicode[Unicode] values with the *Alt* key followed by `+` on the num-block and then the number.

  The following simple batch file (or command) can be executed in → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`] to set this registry value:
  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Control Panel/Input Method/EnableHexNumpad.bat||

  As per → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unicode_input#In_Microsoft_Windows[Wikipedia], users need to log off and sign in again to for this change to take effect.

}
sa:
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Control-Panel[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel`]
